terms.section_6_body:
When placing an order, you:
(1) add products to the cart;
(2) proceed to checkout;
(3) enter your contact and address details;
(4) select delivery or pickup method;
(5) confirm acceptance of the Terms and Privacy Policy;
(6) submit the order.

After submitting the order, you will receive an automatic email confirmation of order receipt. This email confirms receipt of your order but does not guarantee availability of all products. The final contract is deemed concluded after we accept and process your order (e.g., confirm it and begin assembly/shipment).

terms.section_8_body:
Unlike EU legislation, Swiss law does not provide for a general automatic right of withdrawal and return of goods for online purchases (there is no guaranteed 14-day "right of return"). This means you cannot return a product without reason just because you changed your mind.

We accept returns or exchanges only in the following cases:
– the product has a manufacturing defect;
– the product was damaged during delivery;
– the wrong product was delivered;
– for a specific product, the product page explicitly states voluntary return is possible.

If one of these cases applies, you must notify us within a reasonable time, typically within 7 days of receiving the product, describe the problem, and provide photos if possible. We will provide you with return instructions. Products returned due to defect or incorrect delivery should generally be returned in original packaging and, as far as possible, in original condition, except where defect or damage prevents this.

After receiving and inspecting the returned product, we may offer:
– product replacement;
– repair (if applicable);
– refund of product cost. Refunds are made to the same payment method used for purchase unless otherwise agreed.

terms.section_9_body:
Warranty obligations are governed by the Swiss Code of Obligations (OR). The customer must notify us of a defect within a reasonable time after it is discovered. The warranty covers substantial defects that existed at the time of delivery to the customer.

The warranty does not cover:
– natural wear and tear;
– damage caused by improper use or storage;
– external influences beyond our control;
– minor differences or imperfections that do not affect functional properties.
